    <string name="service_desc_short">Status uses this accessibility service to detect screen updates and notifications on older devices.</string>
    <string name="service_desc_long"><![CDATA[Status allows users to customize their status bar for better readability, aesthetic, or functionality, allowing them easier and faster use of their devices. \n\nStatus requires this accessibility service to detect the current app that is displaying on the screen in order to adapt to its color scheme and layout. It also uses this service to listen for notifications on older devices that do not have the NotificationListenerService API.]]></string>
    <string name="majida_desc">Created Chinese translations for this app.</string>
    <string name="preference_prevent_icon_overlap">Prevent Icon Overlap</string>
    <string name="preference_prevent_icon_overlap_desc">Prevents icon \"sections\" from overlapping each other when there are too many icons displaying at once. This setting will cause battery drain with too many updates (music player notifications can be particularly taxing, especially if they update once every second), so be careful with it.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_too_many_icons">Running Out Of Space?</string>
    <string name="tutorial_too_many_icons_desc">It appears that there are too many icons in the status bar and it doesn\'t have room to display them all. To prevent them from being cut off, you could enable the \"Prevent Overlap\" option in the settings or increase available space by reducing padding and icon scale.</string>
    <string name="msg_missing_storage_permission">Please grant access to external storage in order to use this functionality.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_missing_permissions">Missing Permissions</string>
    <string name="tutorial_missing_permissions_desc">It appears that some of the permissions required by Status have not been granted. Without these permissions, some functionality may work incorrectly or be disabled. If you have already granted all the permissions and think that there may be an error, you can disable permission checking in the \'other\' section of the settings menu.</string>
    <string name="preference_ignore_permission_checking">Ignore Permission Checking</string>
    <string name="preference_ignore_permission_checking_desc">Only enable this if you are sure that all permissions have been granted and you know what you are doing! This can cause significant problems if used incorrectly.</string>

